text: Clarke County is a county in the American state of Georgia. The county seat of Clarke County is Athens, Georgia. Clarke county was formed on December 5, 1801 and named after Revolutionary War hero Elijah Clarke. The University of Georgia is in Clarke County. At the 2020 census, Clarke county had 128,671 people. ==References== == Other websites == * Official site Category:Georgia (U.S. state) counties Category:1801 establishments in the United States Category:1800s establishments in Georgia (U.S. state)
